Dejean.
</taxonomicName>
Type locality “ 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:952F4535FC033C666E8AFB79FDABFED2:1859A2F8FC033C656F5CFA8EFE57FAD5" box="[346,417,1328,1354]" municipality="Rio Grande" name="Valley" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Valley</location>
of the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[497,635,1328,1354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Rio Grande</collectingMunicipality>
”. 
<typeStatus box="[655,762,1328,1354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Holotype</typeStatus>
female in MCZ (type number 5511); external structure and spermatheca examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[140,1108,1293,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1882: 148" authorityName="Bates" authorityPageNumber="148" authorityYear="1882" box="[140,534,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sallaei">
<emphasis box="[140,340,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidium sallaei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bates HW" box="[347,534,1399,1425]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="41 - 152" refId="ref6009" refString="Bates HW (1882) Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. I. Part 1. In Godman FD, Salvin O (Eds) Biologia Centrali-Americana. Taylor and Francis, London, 41 - 152." type="book chapter" year="1882">Bates, 1882:148</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality not specified, with localities specified in several states of 
<collectingCountry box="[400,484,1434,1460]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">México</collectingCountry>
as well as 
<collectingCountry box="[607,673,1434,1460]" name="Belize" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Belize</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[733,860,1434,1460]" name="Guatemala" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
. 
<typeStatus box="[872,983,1434,1460]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Erwin TL" box="[311,468,1469,1495]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="455 - 496" refId="ref6201" refString="Erwin TL (1982) Small terrestrial ground-beetles of Central America (Carabidae: Bembidiina and Anillina). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 42: 455 - 496." type="journal article" year="1982">Erwin (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in MNHN; external structure and aedeagus examined.
</paragraph>
