</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[140,1108,1293,1671]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName authority="Casey, 1918: 61" authorityName="Casey" authorityPageNumber="61" authorityYear="1918" box="[140,550,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="retectum">
<emphasis box="[140,361,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Bembidion retectum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Casey TL" box="[371,550,1575,1601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref6089" refString="Casey TL (1918) A review of the North American Bembidiinae. Memoirs on the Coleoptera 8: 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1918">Casey, 1918:61</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Type locality St George, 
<collectingRegion box="[851,912,1575,1601]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Utah</collectingRegion>
. 
<typeStatus box="[925,1036,1575,1601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Erwin TL" box="[349,508,1610,1636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" pagination="165 - 187" refId="ref6233" refString="Erwin TL (1984) Studies of the tribe Bembidiini (Coleoptera: Carabidae): lectotype designations and species group assignments for Bembidion species described by Thomas L. Casey and others. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 60: 165 - 187." type="journal article" year="1984">Erwin (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, in USNM (type number 36923); external structure and aedeagus examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[140,1108,167,334]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">
This species is known from Texas, New 
<collectingRegion box="[579,666,167,193]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, Arizona, Utah, and California south at least to 
<collectingRegion box="[225,311,202,228]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[322,409,202,228]" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">México</collectingCountry>
. In the 
<collectingCountry box="[494,644,202,228]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">United States</collectingCountry>
specimens of this species tend to be paler than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[294,452,238,263]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis box="[294,452,238,263]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with some specimens having a pale elytral apex, and with more notable punctures at the base of the pronotum. Male genitalia, female spermathecae, and DNA sequences are distinctive.
</paragraph>
